				\begin{document}$${S}^{\ast }=\frac{1}{{N}_{{\rm{s}}ys}}\mathop{\sum }\limits_{i}^{{N}_{{\rm{s}}ys}}\,\{3/2{(n\cdot {u}_{i})}^{2}-1/2\},$$\end{document}S⁎=1Nsys∑iNsys{3/2(n⋅ui)2−1/2},where the Nsys is the number of GB particles in the system, the n is the director which denotes the average of orientation direction of GB particles, and the ui is the unit vector along the long axis of the GB particle i. The definition of T* is2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
